The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Experts discuss growth
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Experts discuss growth
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Ahluwalia: Action time                                  
	New Delhi, June 19: The Planning Commission today began a consultation process with experts to form a plan to accelerate economic growth to 10 per cent during the 12th Plan (2012-17), up from 8.1 per cent in the current period.        
	This meeting was for consultation with experts for the approach for the Twelfth Plan. We discussed broad issues with experts today, Planning Commission deputy chairman Montek Singh Ahluwalia told reporters after the first meeting to prepare the approach document for the 12th Plan.        
	Besides the members of the commission, the meeting was attended by various experts, including UIDAI chairman Nandan Nilekani, former Nasscom president Kiran Karnik, former Thermax chairperson Anu Aga, former cabinet secretary Naresh Chandra and CPR senior fellow Sanjoy Hazarika.        
	The Prime Minister has asked us that we should aim for a 10 per cent growth in the next plan. Everybody feels and we also think that growth should be inclusive, he said.        
	The average annual growth target for the 11th Plan was scaled down to 8.1 per cent from 9 per cent.                                                                                                                                       
